{"word":"ἀρόω","slug":"ἀρόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀρόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>The Root is <el>ΑΡΟϜ</el>, <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <a href='S:ἄρουρα'><el>ἄρουρα</el></a>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>arvum.</el> \n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to plough</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>arare</el>, <el>οὔτε φυτεύουσιν, οὔτ' ἀρόωσιν</el> (epic for <el>ἀροῦσι</el>) <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>πόντος ἠρόθη δορί</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to sow</i>, <el>ἀροῦν εἰς κήπους</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of the husband, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, of the child, <i>to be begotten</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}